♪ BEST SUMMER ♪

05:28.449 --> 05:31.121
- ♪ EVER ♪
-(shouting)

05:31.121 --> 05:33.874
♪ OH ♪

05:35.506 --> 05:38.379
OH, IT'S A SHAME SUMMERS
IN REAL LIFE HAVE TO END.

05:38.379 --> 05:39.550
SUMMER'S NOT OVER YET.

05:39.550 --> 05:41.171
WE COULD LIGHT A BONFIRE,

05:41.171 --> 05:43.554
EAT SOME S'MORES,
TELL SCARY STORIES.

05:43.554 --> 05:46.967
BRADY, TOMORROW'S
THE FIRST DAY OF SCHOOL.

05:46.967 --> 05:52.102
-I'VE GOT TONS TO DO.
-YEAH, I DO, TOO.

05:52.102 --> 05:54.104
ACTUALLY, NO, I DON'T.

05:54.104 --> 05:56.477
IF I MANAGE TO PUT MY BOARD
SHORTS ON TOMORROW MORNING,

05:56.477 --> 05:58.188
I'LL BE PRETTY STOKED
WITH MYSELF.

05:58.188 --> 06:00.401
(laughs)

06:05.406 --> 06:09.750
MACK, YOU THINK THINGS
WILL BE DIFFERENT
FOR US AT SCHOOL?

06:09.750 --> 06:14.254
WELL, WE WERE IN SCHOOL
ALL LAST YEAR TOGETHER.

06:14.254 --> 06:15.996
YEAH, BUT, AND WE NEVER MET.
THAT'S MY POINT.

06:15.996 --> 06:18.378
WE'VE ONLY KNOWN EACH
OTHER IN THE SUMMER.

06:18.378 --> 06:21.211
BRADY, IT'S US.

06:21.211 --> 06:23.053
WE'LL BE FINE.

06:23.053 --> 06:26.677
(chuckles) YEAH. TOTALLY.

06:29.640 --> 06:32.973
(sighs)

06:32.973 --> 06:35.275
NO. NO, NO, NO, NO, NO, NO, NO.

06:35.275 --> 06:37.978
-WHAT'S WRONG?
-MY NECKLACE.
THE ONE THAT LELA GAVE ME.

06:37.978 --> 06:40.360
THE ONLY THING I HAVE
FROM WET SIDE STORY .
IT'S GONE.

06:40.360 --> 06:42.402
MAYBE IT'S STILL NEARBY.
SHOULD I DIVE FOR IT?

06:42.402 --> 06:44.865
NO, BRADY.

06:44.865 --> 06:46.987
THERE'S NOTHING
WE CAN DO NOW.

06:48.989 --> 06:52.793
-I'M SORRY.
-I SHOULD PROBABLY GO IN.

06:52.793 --> 06:56.126
YEAH. SURE.

07:15.145 --> 07:18.939
-(school bell rings)
-(upbeat pop music plays)

07:22.613 --> 07:25.115
WHOO-HOO!

07:28.659 --> 07:31.952
WHOO! (laughs)

07:31.952 --> 07:35.125
WHOO! WINDY BLUFF! YEAH!

07:35.125 --> 07:39.129
FIRST DAY BACK!
OH, NO WAY!

07:39.129 --> 07:43.634
-(laughs) WHOO!
-YO, DUDE-MAN!

07:43.634 --> 07:45.636
FIRST DAY OF SCHOOL!

07:45.636 --> 07:49.720
(both yell, laugh)

07:49.720 --> 07:52.092
(inhale)

07:52.092 --> 07:55.556
(shouting)

07:55.556 --> 07:57.768
WHAM, WHAM.
BAP, BAP.

07:57.768 --> 07:59.520
-WHOO!
-YEAH.

07:59.520 --> 08:01.862
-TSS, TSS.
-HEY.

08:01.862 --> 08:03.984
WHOO! SHA, BAH!

08:03.984 --> 08:05.946
DUDE, HOW WAS INDONESIA?

08:05.946 --> 08:07.988
OH, MAN,
THE SWELLS WERE NECTAR.

08:07.988 --> 08:10.871
PRIMO PEARLS, MY HOMBRE .
THE WAVES WERE ALL LIKE,
"MUUMA."

08:10.871 --> 08:14.114
AND I WAS LIKE, "BRA!"
I WAS A ONE-MAN STOKE MACHINE
ALL SUMMER LONG.

08:14.114 --> 08:18.749
-AH, MONDO, DUDE.
-BEYOND MONDO, BRO.
BEYOND MONDO.

08:18.749 --> 08:22.172
HOW WAS YOUR SUMMER?
YOU SPEND SOME QUALITY TIME
CARVING UP THE TUBES?

08:22.172 --> 08:25.125
-I MET A GIRL.
-NO WAY.

08:25.125 --> 08:27.217
-YOU TRAPPED A HONEY?
-YEAH.

08:27.217 --> 08:29.429
IS SHE A SUPER-CHILL
SURF CHICK?

08:29.429 --> 08:30.591
YEAH, WELL,
YEAH, SHE SURFS.

08:30.591 --> 08:32.803
SO, SHE'S ONE OF US?
LAID BACK?

08:32.803 --> 08:36.135
YEAH, SHE'S LAID BACK.
ON OCCASION, WHEN SHE SLEEPS.

08:36.135 --> 08:39.519
-PROBABLY.
-EXCELLENT.

08:39.519 --> 08:41.311
I CAN'T WAIT TO MEET
YOUR LITTLE BEACH BUNNY.

08:41.311 --> 08:44.314
YEAH, I MEAN, JUST,
I WOULDN'T CALL
HER THAT, EXACTLY.

08:44.314 --> 08:48.318
RIGHT ON, BRO. RIGHT ON.

08:48.318 --> 08:50.530
THREE-POINTER! (laughs)

08:50.530 --> 08:52.492
OH, OH. LET'S GO.

08:52.492 --> 08:54.454
-(school bell rings)
-Mack: WELCOME BACK, EVERYONE.

08:54.454 --> 08:56.286
BIG SAVE THE BEACH DANCE
THIS WEEKEND.

08:56.286 --> 08:58.999
BUY A TICKET, SAVE A SEAL.
OH, COME ON.

08:58.999 --> 09:01.331
WHO DOESN'T LOVE SEALS?
WELL, SHARKS,
BUT THEY DON'T LIKE ANYONE.

09:01.331 --> 09:03.924
-AH!
-HEY, HOW WAS YOUR SUMMER?

09:03.924 --> 09:07.047
OH, BIG YAWN.
SCIENCE CAMP WAS EPIC,
THE COLLEGE TOUR WAS FAB,

09:07.047 --> 09:09.880
AND DON'T EVEN GET ME
STARTED ON THE STUDENT
GOVERNMENT CONFERENCE.

09:09.880 --> 09:11.471
I'M SO GLAD YOU
CAME BACK THIS YEAR.

09:11.471 --> 09:12.843
I DON'T KNOW
WHAT I WOULD'VE DONE

09:12.843 --> 09:14.134
IF I'D LOST YOU
TO THAT PREP SCHOOL.

09:14.134 --> 09:15.475
YEAH,
I'M GLAD I'M BACK, TOO.

09:15.475 --> 09:17.307
-OH, HERE.
-OH, WHAT'S THIS?

09:17.307 --> 09:19.519
UH, WELL,
I MADE A DEAL WITH MYSELF.

09:19.519 --> 09:21.732
IF I'M STAYING HERE, I'M DOING
THINGS THAT ARE IMPORTANT TO ME.

09:21.732 --> 09:23.233
SO, I STARTED
AN OCEANOGRAPHY CLUB.

09:23.233 --> 09:24.945
WHICH IS SUPER-CONVENIENT,
SINCE OUR SCHOOL

09:24.945 --> 09:26.607
-IS LITERALLY ON THE OCEAN.
-SUPER COOL.

09:26.607 --> 09:28.819
SIGN ME UP. OH!
I HAVE NEWS.

09:28.819 --> 09:33.323
GUESS WHO I HUNG OUT WITH
AT THE STUDENT
GOVERNMENT CONFERENCE?

09:33.323 --> 09:35.826
SPENCER WATKINS.

09:35.826 --> 09:38.038
THE LITERALLY
CUTEST GUY IN SCHOOL.

09:38.038 --> 09:40.160
-MACK.
-BRADY.

09:40.160 --> 09:44.254
-HEY.
-HI. OH, YOU'RE WEARING
FLIP-FLOPS TO SCHOOL.

09:44.254 --> 09:46.837
YEAH, TOTALLY.
THEY'RE MY FANCY ONES.

09:46.837 --> 09:49.630
OH, THIS IS MY BRO, DEVON.

09:49.630 --> 09:51.381
DEVON,
THIS IS MY GIRLFRIEND, MACK.

09:51.381 --> 09:52.633
THIS IS YOUR GIRLFRIEND?

09:52.633 --> 09:54.134
THIS IS YOUR BOYFRIEND.

09:54.134 --> 09:58.388
-YOU SEEM SURPRISED.
-OH, NO, BRO. IT'S COOL.

09:58.388 --> 10:02.182
BOOK-BAG.
IT LOOKS VERY FULL OF BOOKS.

10:02.182 --> 10:05.856
AND HE DOESN'T SEEM
TO HAVE A BAG... AT ALL.

10:05.856 --> 10:08.939
I DO NOT HAVE A BAG.
I DO, HOWEVER, HAVE A PEN.

10:08.939 --> 10:11.942
-(laughs)
-HOW LONG HAS THAT
BEEN IN THERE?

10:13.573 --> 10:16.076
-WANT SOME?
-WHY NOT?

10:17.287 --> 10:18.538
SO, I'LL SEE YOU LATER?

10:18.538 --> 10:20.661
-YEAH, DURING BREAK?
-CAN'T.

10:20.661 --> 10:22.122
-FRENCH STUDY GROUP.
-UH, LUNCH?

10:22.122 --> 10:24.204
-CALCULUS STUDY GROUP.
-AFTER SCHOOL?

10:24.204 --> 10:26.336
OCEANOGRAPHY CLUB DANCE
SUBCOMMITTEE MEETING.

10:27.337 --> 10:28.548
HOW'S EASTER LOOKING FOR YOU?

10:28.548 --> 10:30.090
(school bell rings)

10:30.090 --> 10:32.052
OH, UM, WE HAVE
MARINE BIOLOGY TOGETHER,
RIGHT?

10:32.052 --> 10:34.254
-THIRD PERIOD? SO,
I'LL SEE YOU THEN.
-SURE, YEAH.

10:34.254 --> 10:36.967
-COOL. ALL RIGHT.
-OKAY.

10:36.967 --> 10:39.389
MACK SEEMS
SUPER COOL, BRO.

10:39.389 --> 10:41.471
YEAH, YEAH. SHE IS.

10:41.471 --> 10:43.814
I MEAN, SHE WENT RIGHT
TO CLASS WHEN THE BELL RANG.

10:43.814 --> 10:47.567
DIFFERENT.
BUT TO EACH, THEIR OWN.

10:49.269 --> 10:53.113
(upbeat pop music plays)

10:53.113 --> 10:56.116
WHAT'S UP,
MY PUCKER-FACED LITTLE BUDDY?

10:56.116 --> 10:58.989
-(clears throat)
-SORRY.

10:58.989 --> 11:00.911
SORRY.

11:02.372 --> 11:04.334
HM...

11:06.957 --> 11:08.999
NO.

11:15.055 --> 11:16.717
-HEY.
-HEY.

11:16.717 --> 11:19.469
-WHAT YOU WORKING ON?
-UH, NOTH-- NOTHING.

11:19.469 --> 11:22.803
-OKAY.
-THIS IS FANTASTIC. MACK!

11:22.803 --> 11:25.475
I GOT ALL THE GOOD STUFF.
SCORE!

11:25.475 --> 11:27.017
I'M GONNA GO
FIRE UP THE CENTRIFUGE.

11:27.017 --> 11:29.439
OH. SPENCER.

11:29.439 --> 11:32.152
WOW. HI.

11:33.313 --> 11:34.865
YOU LOOK GREAT.

11:34.865 --> 11:36.316
REALLY, REALLY GREAT.
SUPER GREAT.

11:36.316 --> 11:37.738
PERFECT, EVEN.

11:41.822 --> 11:43.243
UH, THANKS, ALYSSA,
I APPRECIATE IT.

11:43.243 --> 11:45.415
-(glass shatters)
-(Alyssa screams)

11:45.415 --> 11:48.749
SO, MACK, UH, I'M HAPPY
THAT YOU'RE IN THIS CLASS.

11:48.749 --> 11:50.380
I HEARD THAT YOU STARTED
AN OCEANOGRAPHY CLUB.

11:50.380 --> 11:52.632
I'M CHAIRING
THE ENVIRONMENTAL
STUDIES SOCIETY.

11:52.632 --> 11:54.755
REALLY? OH, I WANTED
TO TALK TO YOU GUYS.

11:54.755 --> 11:56.967
I THOUGHT WE COULD WORK TOGETHER
ON SHORELINE WATERSHED ISSUES.

11:56.967 --> 11:59.639
YES. AND MAYBE AN EMPHASIS
ON HABITAT RESTORATION
AND MARINE POLLUTION.

11:59.639 --> 12:02.843
OH, I LOVE POLLUTION!
I MEAN, I DON'T LOVE POLLUTION,

12:02.843 --> 12:04.344
-BUT IT'S AN IMPORTANT ISSUE.
-YEAH.

12:04.344 --> 12:06.476
UH, I'M ALSO THE HEAD OF A CLUB.

12:06.476 --> 12:09.770
IT'S THE, UH, SURF, SURF CLUB.

12:09.770 --> 12:13.693
YOU JUST HANG OUT AND SURF.

12:16.566 --> 12:19.659
-SPENCER, THIS IS BRADY.
-BRADY, IT'S--

12:19.659 --> 12:21.992
I'VE SEEN YOU SURF.
YOU'RE AMAZING, MAN.
IT'S A PLEASURE TO MEET YOU.

12:21.992 --> 12:23.784
-UH...
-UM...

12:23.784 --> 12:25.625
RIGHT, YEAH.

12:30.670 --> 12:32.793
-CENTRIFUGE.
-CHECK.

12:32.793 --> 12:35.255
-METHYLENE BLUE DYE.
-CHECK.

12:35.255 --> 12:37.838
-CULTURED PETRI DISH.
-CHECK.

12:37.838 --> 12:41.972
BEGIN INOCULATION.
LET'S DILUTE THOSE SOLVENTS.
WHOO!

12:41.972 --> 12:44.094
WHOA, COOL.

12:46.346 --> 12:49.769
HERE WE'VE GOT
SOME WEIRD, TUBE-Y THING.

12:49.769 --> 12:52.022
A SQUEEZY-SPONGE.

12:52.022 --> 12:54.314
SOME WET STUFF.

12:54.314 --> 12:57.157
AND A BLUE, CREEPY GLOVE.

12:59.699 --> 13:01.401
-OH, YOU THINK?
-YEAH.

13:01.401 --> 13:04.744
THANKS. I'VE ALWAYS LOVED
BIOLOGY, AND THE OCEAN.

13:04.744 --> 13:09.079
HEY, UH, HAVE YOU CHECKED OUT
THE NEW OCEANOGRAPHY PROGRAM
AT OREGON COASTAL COLLEGE?

13:09.079 --> 13:12.372
YOU GET TO SPEND HALF
A YEAR ON A SHIP AT SEA.

13:12.372 --> 13:14.714
I COULD INTRODUCE YOU
TO THE REP.

13:14.714 --> 13:16.006
THAT'D BE AMAZING.

13:16.006 --> 13:18.378
BRADY.

13:18.378 --> 13:20.300
HOLA.

13:20.300 --> 13:22.012
YOU OKAY, MY MAN?

13:22.012 --> 13:25.305
YEAH. YEAH, I'M GOOD.
TOTALLY.

13:25.305 --> 13:28.889
ALL RIGHT, WELL,
LET'S DO THIS.

13:34.434 --> 13:37.527
OH, WHA--
I MADE A VOLCANO!

13:37.527 --> 13:39.649
-UH, UH...
-THAT'S SO SICK!

13:39.649 --> 13:41.651
OH, GNARLY.

13:41.651 --> 13:45.155
DUDE, LOOK AT THIS!
WHAT?

13:45.155 --> 13:47.537
OH, MY GOSH.

13:49.579 --> 13:51.661
Brady: MACK. MACK.

13:51.661 --> 13:53.503
-HEY.
-HEY.

13:53.503 --> 13:55.715
OH, HEY, BEFORE I FORGET.
WHAT DO YOU THINK OF THIS?

13:55.715 --> 13:57.837
I'M GONNA SELL THEM
AT THE SAVE THE BEACH DANCE.

13:57.837 --> 14:02.382
-I DIG IT.
-GOOD, 'CAUSE I GOT YOU,
LIKE, EIGHT.

14:02.382 --> 14:05.175
WOW. I'M GONNA
NEED A BIGGER WRIST.
THANKS.

14:05.175 --> 14:08.388
HEY, THERE'S A BIG SWELL ON.
WANNA GO SURFING?

14:08.388 --> 14:11.101
OH, THAT SOUNDS AWESOME,
BUT I CAN'T.

14:11.101 --> 14:14.144
THE DANCE IS THIS WEEKEND, AND
WE ARE TOTALLY BEHIND SCHEDULE.

14:14.144 --> 14:16.436
OH, SPEAKING OF,
I HAD THE COOLEST IDEA.

14:16.436 --> 14:19.029
WHAT IF THE DANCE
WAS A 60S
WET SIDE STORY THEME PARTY?

14:19.029 --> 14:21.361
YOU COULD DO IT
AT THE BEACH.

14:21.361 --> 14:22.943
PEOPLE COULD
DRESS UP IN COSTUMES.

14:22.943 --> 14:24.444
YOU COULD EVEN PROJECT
THE MOVIE ON A BIG,

14:24.444 --> 14:25.986
1960S TYPE THEATER DEAL.

14:25.986 --> 14:27.948
-THAT WOULD BE REALLY COOL.
-RIGHT?

14:27.948 --> 14:30.870
BUT THERE'S JUST NO TIME.
AND, AS MUCH AS I LOVE

14:30.870 --> 14:32.752
WET SIDE STORY ,
YOU AND I ARE, LIKE,

14:32.752 --> 14:34.995
THE ONLY PEOPLE UNDER 50
THAT HAVE EVER HEARD OF IT.

14:34.995 --> 14:38.208
YEAH, YOU'RE PROBABLY RIGHT.

14:38.208 --> 14:40.380
OH, THE COLLEGE FAIR LATER.
YOU'RE GOING WITH ME, RIGHT?

14:40.380 --> 14:43.303
RIGHT. YEAH. UH-HUH.

14:43.303 --> 14:46.716
BRADY, THIS IS IMPORTANT.
IT'S COLLEGE. IT'S OUR FUTURE.

14:46.716 --> 14:51.681
AND THERE'S THIS AMAZING
OCEANOGRAPHY PROGRAM
THAT I HAVE TO CHECK OUT.

14:51.681 --> 14:53.683
YES, OF COURSE.
I'LL BE THERE.

14:53.683 --> 14:57.017
-IN ACTUAL SHOES?
-SURE.

14:57.017 --> 14:59.019
-(laughs)
-OKAY.

14:59.019 --> 15:01.731
-YEAH. SEE YOU.
-BYE.

15:02.943 --> 15:05.115
GUESS I'LL GO SURF BY MYSELF.

15:06.987 --> 15:09.409
-BRADY.
-HEY, BRO.

15:15.035 --> 15:16.706
WHOA.

15:22.422 --> 15:26.426
OKAY. UNIVERSAL ONLINE
COLLEGE APPLICATION.

15:26.426 --> 15:29.309
HM... "WHAT PERSONAL ATTRIBUTES

15:29.309 --> 15:34.104
UNIQUELY QUALIFY YOU
AS AN EXTRAORDINARY APPLICANT?"

15:34.104 --> 15:36.936
ARE YOU KIDDING ME?

15:39.649 --> 15:42.022
♪ It's a bikini wonderland ♪

15:42.022 --> 15:43.773
♪ Summer's on... ♪

15:54.374 --> 15:59.919
LET'S SEE.
DEEPER BOTTOM CURVE,
NOT ON STEEP WAVES.

15:59.919 --> 16:02.632
HOW DO YOU INCREASE
WATER DISPLACEMENT
SO IT RIDES SMOOTHER?

16:02.632 --> 16:04.384
-(tapping)
-HEY, MOM.

16:04.384 --> 16:08.348
-HOW'S THAT GOING?
-IT'S GOING.

16:08.348 --> 16:10.510
SLOWLY. VERY SLOWLY.

16:12.092 --> 16:16.056
MM... WOW.
HOW'S THAT GOING?

16:16.056 --> 16:18.058
IT'S GOING.

16:18.058 --> 16:20.650
I MEAN, I'VE OPENED IT UP.
I'VE STARED AT IT.

16:20.650 --> 16:24.104
MM. WELL, DON'T STRESS
YOURSELF OUT TOO MUCH.

16:24.104 --> 16:25.655
YEAH.

16:27.657 --> 16:31.571
IT'S JUST,
EVERYONE SEEMS SO FOCUSED.

16:31.571 --> 16:34.074
THEY'VE GOT THEIR
WHOLE LIVES MAPPED OUT.
LIKE MACK.

16:34.074 --> 16:36.956
SHE KNOWS WHERE SHE WANTS TO GO,
WHAT SHE WANTS TO DO.

16:36.956 --> 16:41.961
AND I... I DON'T EVEN KNOW
WHAT I WANT FOR DINNER.

16:41.961 --> 16:45.715
THINGS WERE A LITTLE ROUGH WITH
YOU TWO BACK AT SCHOOL TODAY?

16:47.467 --> 16:49.259
NO.

16:51.301 --> 16:52.932
OKAY, MAYBE.

16:54.264 --> 16:55.895
YEAH.

16:55.895 --> 17:00.850
HAVE YOU SEEN MY BROWN MARKER?
I CAN'T FIND IT.

17:00.850 --> 17:03.983
-OH.
-(chuckles)

17:03.983 --> 17:07.906
I'M SURE THINGS ARE GONNA
WORK OUT BETWEEN YOU TWO.

17:07.906 --> 17:09.909
OKAY?

17:09.909 --> 17:12.452
AND BRING THESE
WET TOWELS DOWNSTAIRS.

17:12.452 --> 17:13.992
SURE, MOM.

17:13.992 --> 17:16.996
DINNER'S BACK AT THE HOUSE
AT SIX.

17:16.996 --> 17:19.829
So, Tanner, is you's and me's
ready to disarm

17:19.829 --> 17:21.501
the diabolical
weather machine now?

17:21.501 --> 17:23.752
You bet, daddio.
Ready is my middle name.

17:23.752 --> 17:26.086
Ready!
It's his middle name.

17:26.086 --> 17:27.627
I thought Lewis
was your middle name.

17:27.627 --> 17:29.469
It is Lewis,
but it's also ready.

17:29.469 --> 17:31.591
'Cause that's
what I was born.

17:31.591 --> 17:33.303
-READY.
-READY!

17:33.303 --> 17:35.385
FROM THE MOMENT HE WAS BORN.

17:35.385 --> 17:39.139
DON'T GO, TANNER.
IT'S SO DANGEROUS.

17:39.139 --> 17:42.772
DON'T WORRY.
DANGER IS ALSO MY MIDDLE NAME.

17:42.772 --> 17:45.315
-MM-HM.
-I THINK.

17:45.315 --> 17:47.066
ALONG WITH READY AND LEWIS.

17:47.066 --> 17:50.320
-THAT IS A VERY LONG NAME.
-(giggles)

17:50.320 --> 17:53.032
OKAY, TANNER.

17:53.032 --> 17:56.956
I'LL JUST WAIT RIGHT HERE
FOR YOU, AND--

17:56.956 --> 17:58.618
WELL, ACTUALLY,
WHY DON'T I COME, TOO?

17:58.618 --> 18:02.622
-(needle scratches on record)
-OH.

18:02.622 --> 18:04.754
UH, WHAT?

18:04.754 --> 18:07.877
-WHY DON'T I COME WITH YOU?
-(all gasp)

18:07.877 --> 18:10.260
I MEAN, ALL THAT HAPPENS
WHEN YOU GUYS GO OFF

18:10.260 --> 18:13.513
IS WE STAND HERE
AND DO NOTHING.
MAYBE I CAN HELP.

18:13.513 --> 18:17.637
-Girl: WHAT?
-UH, JUST ONE-- EXCUSE US.

18:17.637 --> 18:19.098
(laughs)

18:19.098 --> 18:22.222
UM, BUT GIRLS
AREN'T SUPPOSED TO.

18:24.854 --> 18:26.065
RIGHT. I'M SORRY.

18:26.065 --> 18:27.647
I DON'T KNOW
WHERE THAT CAME FROM.

18:27.647 --> 18:30.440
-FORGET ABOUT IT.
-(all murmuring)

18:32.572 --> 18:34.944
(panting) OKAY.

18:34.944 --> 18:37.697
GO, TANNER. BE SAFE.

18:37.697 --> 18:40.410
BE BRAVE.

18:40.410 --> 18:42.582
YOU'RE MY HERO.

18:45.004 --> 18:46.506
LET'S GO!

18:46.506 --> 18:50.250
-(all shouting)
-(surf rock plays)

18:54.214 --> 18:56.886
-Girl: COME BACK SOON!
-Girl 2: SO BRAVE.

19:06.316 --> 19:10.900
-(thunder rumbles)
-WHAT WAS...

19:14.234 --> 19:15.405
NO!

19:15.405 --> 19:18.408
NO, NO.

19:18.408 --> 19:19.619
YES!

19:19.619 --> 19:21.701
(gasps) NO!

19:21.701 --> 19:24.584
-THANKS, GRANDMA.
-♪ I GOT SOMETHING ♪

19:24.584 --> 19:26.085
♪ ON MY MIND ♪

19:26.085 --> 19:28.288
♪ SOMEDAY SOON
GONNA MAKE YOU MINE ♪

19:28.288 --> 19:31.000
♪ TONGUE-TIED, TWISTED
INSIDE OUT ♪

19:31.000 --> 19:33.923
-GRANDMA?
-♪ GOT NO CHOICE
I'M GONNA SCREAM AND SHOUT ♪

19:33.923 --> 19:35.885
-YES!
-♪ COME ON ♪

19:36.886 --> 19:38.388
♪ COME ON ♪

19:38.388 --> 19:40.430
WHAT? OH!

19:42.222 --> 19:44.264
YES. WHOO!

19:48.478 --> 19:51.901
♪ NOW I KNOW
JUST WHAT I WANT ♪

19:54.153 --> 19:57.817
♪ LOOKING SO RIGHT
THAT YOU KNOW IT'S WRONG ♪

20:03.082 --> 20:06.536
(thunder crashes)

20:08.498 --> 20:10.920
-THANK YOU SO MUCH
FOR TALKING TO ME.
-A PLEASURE.

20:10.920 --> 20:13.713
IT WAS GREAT MEETING YOU, MACK.
I HOPE YOU'LL APPLY.

20:13.713 --> 20:16.636
-NICE MEETING YOU, TOO.
-YOU, TOO.

20:16.636 --> 20:18.798
YOU'RE RIGHT.
THIS PROGRAM IS AWESOME.

20:18.798 --> 20:21.601
-I KNEW YOU'D LOVE IT.
-Brady: MACK.

20:26.185 --> 20:27.397
WHAT'S GOING ON?

20:28.848 --> 20:31.851
BRADY, IT'S ALREADY OVER.
WHERE WERE YOU?

20:33.693 --> 20:36.356
LISTEN, UH,
I BETTER BE GOING.

20:36.356 --> 20:39.359
IN CASE YOU NEED IT.

20:39.359 --> 20:41.701
I WILL SEE
YOU GUYS TOMORROW.

20:45.244 --> 20:47.497
Brady: YOU KNOW, YOU COULD'VE
AT LEAST SHOT ME A TEXT.

20:47.497 --> 20:49.128
-I DID. TWELVE.
-NO, YOU DIDN'T.

20:49.128 --> 20:52.582
-YEAH, CHECK YOUR PHONE.
-WHAT?

20:52.582 --> 20:55.174
IS IT TOO MUCH FOR YOU
TO TAKE ONE THING SERIOUSLY?

20:55.174 --> 20:58.718
-AT LEAST I TAKE US SERIOUSLY.
-WHAT? I TAKE US SERIOUSLY.

20:58.718 --> 21:02.091
YOU WERE 45 MINUTES LATE.
WHAT WERE YOU DOING?
DID YOU JUST FORGET?

21:02.091 --> 21:04.684
I WAS-- IT WAS NOTHING.

21:04.684 --> 21:07.186
-NOTHING?
-SOMETHING.
I DON'T WANNA TALK ABOUT IT.

21:07.186 --> 21:09.098
WELL, YOU WON'T EVEN
TELL ME WHY YOU STOOD ME UP?

21:09.098 --> 21:10.810
BRADY, WE USED TO TELL
EACH OTHER EVERYTHING.

21:10.810 --> 21:12.352
-WHAT IS HAPPENING WITH US?
-YOU TELL ME.

21:12.352 --> 21:13.943
IT'S ALMOST LIKE
THE SCHOOL-YOU WANTS

21:13.943 --> 21:15.815
-NOTHING TO DO WITH ME.
-THIS COMING FROM THE SCHOOL-YOU

21:15.815 --> 21:17.357
THAT KEEPS SECRETS
AND FLAKES OUT ON ME.

21:17.357 --> 21:18.988
WELL, MAYBE WE JUST
DON'T WORK AT SCHOOL.

21:18.988 --> 21:20.700
-MAYBE WE DON'T.
-AWESOME.

21:20.700 --> 21:23.072
AWESOME.
SO, I'LL SEE YOU NEXT SUMMER,

21:23.072 --> 21:25.204
WHICH, APPARENTLY,
IS THE NEXT TIME YOU'RE FREE.

21:25.204 --> 21:29.168
-FINE BY ME.
-GREAT. AH, THAT'S JUST AWESOME.

21:42.051 --> 21:44.844
♪ IT ALMOST FEELS
LIKE IT WAS JUST A DREAM ♪

21:44.844 --> 21:47.637
♪ ALL THESE MEMORIES
OF YOU AND ME ♪

21:47.637 --> 21:53.062
♪ BLOWN AWAY
IN THE SUMMER BREEZE ♪

21:53.062 --> 21:55.645
♪ IT ALMOST FEELS
LIKE WE JUST NEVER WERE ♪

21:55.645 --> 21:58.398
♪ ALL THAT TIME
WE SPENT WAS JUST A BLUR ♪

21:58.398 --> 22:02.862
♪ NOW IT'S JUST ME
AND A MELODY ♪

22:02.862 --> 22:05.204
♪ SO WHAT AM I ♪

22:05.204 --> 22:07.657
♪ SUPPOSED TO DO? ♪

22:07.657 --> 22:09.869
♪ 'CAUSE ALL THESE PLANS ♪

22:09.869 --> 22:13.833
♪ WE MADE IN THE SAND
ARE THROUGH ♪

22:16.456 --> 22:21.050
♪ WITHOUT YOU, I'M ON MY OWN ♪

22:21.050 --> 22:23.803
♪ AM I GONNA BE ALONE ♪

22:23.803 --> 22:26.886
♪ AND IF IT'S ONLY ME,
MYSELF AND I ♪

22:26.886 --> 22:28.728
♪ WILL I BE FINE? ♪

22:28.728 --> 22:31.811
♪ SO FAR FROM HOME ♪

22:31.811 --> 22:33.683
♪ AND I JUST DON'T KNOW ♪

22:33.683 --> 22:35.144
♪ AM I GONNA MAKE IT? ♪

22:35.144 --> 22:37.777
♪ BRAVE ENOUGH
TO TAKE THIS ROAD ♪

22:37.777 --> 22:41.070
♪ OUT ON MY OWN? ♪

22:42.902 --> 22:44.444
(playing drumbeat)

22:44.444 --> 22:48.748
(rock music playing)

22:55.415 --> 22:57.957
♪ AND MAYBE I'M FALLING
ON MY FACE ♪

22:57.957 --> 23:00.760
♪ OR MAYBE I'M
LANDING IN MY PLACE ♪

23:00.760 --> 23:03.262
♪ AND MAYBE WE'RE
A MILLION MILES APART ♪

23:03.262 --> 23:06.055
♪ OR MAYBE WE'RE
STANDING HEART TO HEART ♪

23:06.055 --> 23:08.768
♪ BUT NO MATTER
WHAT I'M WALKING
RIGHT OFF THIS STAGE ♪

23:08.768 --> 23:13.272
♪ AND NEVER LOOKING BACK,
LOOKING BACK TO YESTERDAY ♪

23:13.272 --> 23:15.975
♪ NO WAY ♪

23:15.975 --> 23:18.728
♪ NO WAY ♪

23:18.728 --> 23:22.281
♪ I'M ON MY OWN ♪

23:22.281 --> 23:26.285
♪ YEAH, YEAH, YEAH ♪

23:26.285 --> 23:29.909
♪ AS LONG AS I GOT
ME, MYSELF AND I ♪

23:29.909 --> 23:31.491
♪ I'M DOING FINE ♪

23:31.491 --> 23:34.373
♪ SO FAR FROM HOME ♪

23:34.373 --> 23:37.457
♪ BUT NOW I KNOW
THAT I AM GONNA MAKE IT ♪

23:37.457 --> 23:40.500
♪ BRAVE ENOUGH
TO TAKE THIS ROAD ♪

23:40.500 --> 23:43.593
♪ OUT ON MY OWN ♪

23:47.386 --> 23:50.550
♪ IT ALMOST FEELS
LIKE IT WAS JUST A DREAM ♪

23:50.550 --> 23:54.684
♪ ALL THESE MEMORIES
OF YOU AND ME ♪

23:57.557 --> 24:01.320
Girl on TV: ♪ I'M NOT THE KIND
TO FALL FOR A GUY ♪

24:01.320 --> 24:04.614
♪ WHO FLASHES A SMILE ♪

24:04.614 --> 24:08.027
♪ DON'T USUALLY SWOON
BUT I'M OVER THE MOON ♪

24:08.027 --> 24:12.622
- ♪ 'CAUSE HE WAS
JUST TOO COOL FOR SCHOOL ♪
- ♪ AND NOW I'M ♪

24:12.622 --> 24:16.666
-(gasps)
-NICE OF YOU TO DROP IN.

24:16.666 --> 24:20.039
I GUESS I LITERALLY
FELL FOR YOU, HUH?

24:20.039 --> 24:21.631
(dings)

24:21.631 --> 24:23.503
♪ FALLING FOR YOU ♪

24:23.503 --> 24:26.045
I'M LELA.
I'M SORRY, I CAN'T DO THIS.

24:26.045 --> 24:27.547
-PUT ME DOWN.
-(needle scratches record)

24:27.547 --> 24:32.301
-(crashing)
-(murmuring)

24:35.474 --> 24:37.226
UH, LELA.

24:37.226 --> 24:41.811
(laughs) WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

24:41.811 --> 24:45.274
I DON'T KNOW.
THIS WHOLE THING, I JUST...

24:45.274 --> 24:47.446
I CAN'T DO IT ANYMORE.

24:47.446 --> 24:49.949
IT'S NOT YOU, TANNER.
YOU'RE A GREAT GUY, BUT--

24:49.949 --> 24:52.071
OF COURSE I AM.

24:54.113 --> 24:55.454
I HAVE TO GO.

25:05.294 --> 25:11.891
-WHERE IS SHE GOING?
-UH... (laughs)

25:11.891 --> 25:15.184
OKAY. EXCUSE ME, GUYS.
EXCUSE ME. SORRY.

25:18.848 --> 25:20.519
LELA!

25:28.317 --> 25:29.779
WHAT'S GOING ON?

25:29.779 --> 25:32.992
WHAT ARE WE DOING?

25:32.992 --> 25:35.454
IT'S VERY WINDY
AND NOT GOOD FOR MY HAIR.

25:35.454 --> 25:39.118
EVER SINCE MACK AND BRADY CAME,
I HAVE FELT DIFFERENT.

25:39.118 --> 25:42.421
MACK WASN'T LIKE
ANY GIRL I EVER KNEW.
SHE INSPIRED ME.

25:42.421 --> 25:45.464
I... I MISS HER.

25:45.464 --> 25:48.628
I MISS HER, TOO.
AND BRADY. I--
THEY WERE SWELL.

25:48.628 --> 25:51.801
BUT, UH, BUT THEY'RE
NOT HERE ANYMORE.

25:51.801 --> 25:54.553
-I WANT TO BE
LIKE HER, TANNER.
-WHAT?

25:54.553 --> 25:58.848
TRY NEW THINGS.
EXPERIENCE NEW EXPERIENCES.

26:04.684 --> 26:07.356
WHAT IS THAT?

26:10.109 --> 26:13.192
(gasps) TANNER, LOOK.

26:13.192 --> 26:15.454
DO YOU KNOW WHAT THIS IS?

26:15.454 --> 26:19.368
UH, A NECKLACE.

26:19.368 --> 26:22.792
I GAVE IT TO MACK.

26:22.792 --> 26:26.465
AND IT CAME BACK
TO ME HERE, NOW.
DON'T YOU SEE?

26:26.465 --> 26:28.047
IT'S A SIGN.

26:30.299 --> 26:32.842
IT REALLY LOOKS LIKE A NECKLACE.

26:32.842 --> 26:36.886
THIS MEANS SHE'S
OUT THERE SOMEWHERE.

26:36.886 --> 26:39.849
I NEED TO BE WHERE SHE IS.

26:41.430 --> 26:43.352
GOODBYE, TANNER.

26:43.352 --> 26:45.685
WHA-- WHAT?

26:45.685 --> 26:47.186
OH.

26:47.186 --> 26:49.939
GOODBYE, BIKERS.

26:49.939 --> 26:51.941
GOODBYE, SURFERS.

26:51.941 --> 26:54.734
GOODBYE, PEOPLE ALWAYS STANDING
AROUND IN THE BACKGROUND,
WHO NEVER SPEAK,

26:54.734 --> 26:56.946
WHOSE NAMES I DON'T KNOW.

27:00.950 --> 27:03.002
-UH...
-(all gasp)

27:03.002 --> 27:05.544
-(grunting)
-(all gasp)

27:05.544 --> 27:08.668
-WE GOTTA STOP HER, RIGHT?
-I MEAN, WE DEFINITELY COULD.

27:08.668 --> 27:10.960
-BUT WATER MAKES ME
A LITTLE BIT NERVOUS.
-WHAT?

27:10.960 --> 27:13.462
-I KNOW.
-MAYBE WE SHOULD SING A SONG.
THAT USUALLY FIXES EVERYTHING.

27:13.462 --> 27:15.384
♪ I'M FALLING FOR- - ♪
NO, NO.

27:15.384 --> 27:17.516
UH, MAYBE I'LL TALK
IN MY LOW VOICE.

27:17.516 --> 27:19.518
LELA, COME BACK.

27:19.518 --> 27:22.561
YEAH, MAYBE I'D SAVE
THE LOW VOICE FOR SOMEONE
WHO CAN ACTUALLY HEAR YOU.

27:22.561 --> 27:24.764
SHE'S ALREADY IN THE OCEAN.

27:26.025 --> 27:28.317
(whimpering)

27:30.029 --> 27:31.320
AW, WHERE'S THEY GOINS?

27:31.320 --> 27:33.482
LELA! OH!

27:33.482 --> 27:35.945
(all gasp)

27:37.116 --> 27:40.659
(all murmuring)

27:50.960 --> 27:52.962
Lela: JEEPERS.

27:54.553 --> 27:56.555
-Tanner: OH, MY.
-Lela: TANNER.

27:56.555 --> 28:00.349
-WHAT ARE YOU DOING HERE?
-I DON'T KNOW. (laughs)

28:02.641 --> 28:04.433
ARE YOU OKAY?
I'M OKAY.

28:04.433 --> 28:06.726
IT'S A LITTLE HOT OUTSIDE.
I DON'T KNOW WHAT TO DO.
WHERE ARE WE?

28:06.726 --> 28:08.687
-(gasps) WHY IS IT
SO HOT OUTSIDE?
-TANNER.

28:08.687 --> 28:10.439
-TANNER.
-WHAT?

28:10.439 --> 28:12.071
(water spraying)

28:17.526 --> 28:19.368
OH, MY.

28:21.781 --> 28:23.953
Lela: OH!

28:26.125 --> 28:27.456
WELL, JEEPERS.

28:27.456 --> 28:29.628
-AH!
-OH!

28:29.628 --> 28:31.170
-LET'S GET OUR BOARDS.
-ALL RIGHT.

28:31.170 --> 28:32.752
THOSE FELLAS
ARE MADE OF RUBBER!

28:32.752 --> 28:34.884
OH, GOLLY.

28:34.884 --> 28:37.136
(rock music playing)

28:39.969 --> 28:44.053
WHOO-HOO!

28:44.053 --> 28:47.897
WHOO-HOO-HOO!
WHOO-HOO-HOO-HOO!

28:49.058 --> 28:51.110
WHOA!

28:52.441 --> 28:54.653
JEEPERS.

28:56.235 --> 28:58.067
-IS THAT BIG MOMMA'S?
-HUH?

28:58.067 --> 28:59.408
NO, IT'S, UH,

28:59.408 --> 29:04.413
BILLY'S BEACH BURGERS
AND SHA...

29:04.413 --> 29:06.745
SHUSHI. WHAT'S A SHUSHI?
WHERE ARE WE?

29:06.745 --> 29:08.828
I DON'T KNOW. WE-- OH.
EXCUSE ME.

29:08.828 --> 29:12.291
-HEY. WHAT'S HAPPENING?
-OH. SO-- (laughs)

29:12.291 --> 29:15.174
SO WE WENT INTO THE WATER
AND THEN CAME OUT OF THE WATER,

29:15.174 --> 29:17.797
AND NOW IT'S DAYTIME,
AND WE SAW RUBBER PEOPLE,
AND BOAT CYCLES--

29:17.797 --> 29:21.180
-I THINK WE'RE LOST.
-HERE. USE MY PHONE.

