NEW THINGS, AND THEN
I WAS SITTING THERE,

52:29.227 --> 52:30.898
AND I'M LIKE, "HEY,
WHY DON'T I MAKE A NEW LOOK?"

52:30.898 --> 52:33.361
SO, I MADE A NEW LOOK,
AND IT WAS RENEGADE REBEL,
YOU KNOW?

52:33.361 --> 52:37.825
(laughing) AND THEN--
WHAT WAS THE OTHER ONE?
I CAN'T THINK OF WHAT IT WAS.

52:39.447 --> 52:42.580
OH, YEAH.
MYSTERIOUS WANDERER.

52:42.580 --> 52:44.121
AND THEN, UH, THINKING GUY.

52:44.121 --> 52:45.743
(laughs, screams)

52:45.743 --> 52:50.918
-HERE. CHECK THIS OUT.
-OH, THANKS. MM.

52:53.461 --> 52:57.425
OH. HI, MEDIUM-SIZED ME.
(laughs)

53:00.137 --> 53:01.429
STILL LOOKING GOOD.

53:20.408 --> 53:24.322
-BRADY, CAN I TALK
TO YOU FOR A SECOND?
-YEAH, SURE.

53:24.322 --> 53:28.496
UM, I'VE BEEN THINKING
ABOUT THINGS.

53:28.496 --> 53:31.749
AND I DON'T NORMALLY LIKE
TO THINK ABOUT THINGS.

53:31.749 --> 53:32.960
(chuckles)

53:34.382 --> 53:36.594
(clears throat) YOU SEE...

53:37.755 --> 53:40.718
I ALWAYS ASSUMED
LELA WOULD JUST
BE THERE FOR ME.

53:41.759 --> 53:43.761
BUT...

53:43.761 --> 53:47.395
THAT NIGHT WHEN
SHE RAN INTO THE WATER
WITH HER NECKLACE,

53:47.395 --> 53:49.847
IT GAVE ME
THIS STRANGE FEELING
IN MY STOMACH.

53:50.848 --> 53:52.310
IT FELT LIKE,

53:52.310 --> 53:55.353
LIKE WHEN I DRINK
A MILKSHAKE TOO FAST.
(laughs)

53:55.353 --> 53:56.484
(chuckles)

53:56.484 --> 53:59.527
IT FELT LIKE,

53:59.527 --> 54:01.569
LIKE THINGS,

54:01.569 --> 54:05.202
MIGHT NOT WORK OUT.

54:06.824 --> 54:10.037
(chuckles)
IT'S CALLED WORRY.

54:10.037 --> 54:11.789
YEAH, YEAH. THAT.

54:13.170 --> 54:16.213
AND, THE THING IS,
THINGS ALWAYS WORK OUT FOR ME.

54:19.377 --> 54:23.090
BUT, HERE, NOW,
I-- I STILL HAVE THAT FEELING.

54:24.141 --> 54:26.053
-WORRY?
-YEAH. YEAH.

54:28.265 --> 54:32.480
I'M WORRIED THAT LELA WANTED
TO COME TO THIS STRANGE WORLD
BECAUSE I WASN'T ENOUGH FOR HER.

54:33.891 --> 54:35.192
(chuckles)

54:39.567 --> 54:40.988
YEAH.

54:45.072 --> 54:48.576
I MEAN, I GUESS
ALL YOU CAN REALLY DO

54:48.576 --> 54:52.410
IS BE THE BEST
DUDE YOU CAN BE
AND HOPE THAT'S ENOUGH.

54:53.541 --> 54:55.042
IS THAT WHAT
YOU DO WITH MACK?

54:56.123 --> 54:59.677
UM, NOT--
NOT RECENTLY, NO.

55:01.298 --> 55:03.300
WE KIND OF HIT
A ROUGH PATCH.

55:05.343 --> 55:08.426
I'VE BEEN WORKING
ON SOMETHING I HAVEN'T
TOLD HER ABOUT YET.

55:08.426 --> 55:09.847
WHAT IS IT?

55:11.479 --> 55:14.101
(chuckles) COME ON.

55:17.645 --> 55:21.108
-ARE THESE SURFBOARDS?
-YEAH. THEY'RE ALL SURFBOARDS,
BUT PROTOTYPES.

55:21.108 --> 55:23.030
LIKE THIS ONE.
IT HAS ROTATING FINS,

55:23.030 --> 55:24.532
SO YOU CAN SURF
IN ANY DIRECTION.

55:24.532 --> 55:26.944
OR THIS ONE.
IT'S ONE OF MY FAVORITES.

55:26.944 --> 55:29.156
IT'S MY SURFBOARD SUITCASE.

55:29.156 --> 55:31.288
SO, YOU FOLD UP YOUR BOARD,
PUT IT IN YOUR BAG,

55:31.288 --> 55:33.541
AND IT GOES UP
IN THE CARRY-ON,
THEN, WHEN YOU LAND,

55:34.712 --> 55:37.084
-YOU'RE READY TO SURF.
-THAT IS SO COOL!

55:37.084 --> 55:40.167
-YEAH.
-WAIT, Y--
SO, YOU MADE ALL THIS STUFF?

55:40.167 --> 55:43.170
-UH-HUH.
-I'VE NEVER MADE ANYTHING.
WHAT'S ALL THIS STUFF?

55:43.170 --> 55:45.302
THIS ONE'S CRAZY.

55:45.302 --> 55:47.054
SO, YOU HAVE
TWO WATER INTAKES

55:47.054 --> 55:48.886
THAT LEADS
TO THE SEALED HYDRO-TURBINE

55:48.886 --> 55:50.968
THAT ALSO GOES
TO AN INTERNAL
LITHIUM ION BATTERY.

55:50.968 --> 55:55.142
THEN, WE HAVE
A PNEUMATIC ACTUATOR
THAT'S CONNECTED TO THIS HATCH,

55:55.142 --> 55:58.105
THAT MAKES IT OPEN
WHENEVER I WANT IT TO.

55:58.105 --> 56:01.188
UH, EVERYTHING
YOU JUST SAID,

56:01.188 --> 56:03.320
I HAVE NO IDEA
WHAT IT MEANS.

56:03.320 --> 56:04.902
(both chuckle)

56:04.902 --> 56:08.616
BASICALLY, THIS SURFBOARD
DOESN'T NEED ANY WAVES.

56:10.157 --> 56:12.249
WELL, THAT IS, IF IT WORKS.

56:12.249 --> 56:14.371
THAT'S SO COOL.

56:14.371 --> 56:16.333
WHY CAN'T YOU TELL MACK?

56:19.256 --> 56:22.590
BECAUSE...
I DON'T THINK
SHE'LL GET IT.

56:22.590 --> 56:26.173
YOU KNOW, ME SPENDING
SO MUCH TIME ON SURFBOARDS.

56:26.173 --> 56:28.766
SHE'S GOT
HER WHOLE LIFE MAPPED OUT.
SHE WANTS TO GO TO COLLEGE.

56:28.766 --> 56:30.848
COLLEGE? WHAT'S IT--

56:30.848 --> 56:34.011
WHERE IS IT-- WHAT'S A--
WHERE'S A COLLEGE?

56:34.011 --> 56:36.063
(sighs)
IT'S FAR AWAY.

56:36.063 --> 56:38.145
AND IT'S FULL
OF IMPRESSIVE PEOPLE,
LIKE HER.

56:38.145 --> 56:40.017
IT'S-- IT'S NOT A PLACE
WHERE A GUY LIKE ME

56:40.017 --> 56:41.729
COULD GET AROUND
BY MAKING SURFBOARDS.

56:41.729 --> 56:43.821
I UNDERSTAND, BRADY.

56:43.821 --> 56:48.986
MAYBE THE PROBLEM IS THAT
YOU'RE NOT TAN ENOUGH.

56:48.986 --> 56:50.828
(both laugh)

56:56.243 --> 57:00.127
MACK, I NEVER KNEW
I COULD BE SO HAPPY.

57:04.001 --> 57:06.343
I MEAN, I LOVE IT ALL,

57:06.343 --> 57:09.717
THE CHALLENGING CLASSES,
THE INTERESTING CONVERSATIONS,

57:09.717 --> 57:11.679
THE FLAVORED LIP GLOSS.

57:11.679 --> 57:14.221
I MEAN, REALLY.
TRIPLE VANILLA KIWI BERRY?

57:14.221 --> 57:16.223
(both laugh)

57:16.223 --> 57:18.435
I NEVER EVEN KNEW THERE WAS
MORE THAN ONE VANILLA.

57:19.607 --> 57:21.939
-CAN I--
-YEAH.

57:21.939 --> 57:26.824
UH, LELA, HERE'S THE THING.
OUR WORLD ISN'T REALLY
ALL THAT GREAT.

57:26.824 --> 57:30.568
OH, THERE'S FINALS,
AND TAXES, AND GLOBAL WARMING,

57:30.568 --> 57:32.910
AND HANGNAILS,
AND PUBLIC RESTROOMS.

57:34.031 --> 57:36.243
YOU REALLY HAD IT GOOD
BACK IN YOUR WORLD.

57:36.243 --> 57:40.457
YOU DON'T HAVE
TO WORRY ABOUT YOUR FUTURE
OR PICKING THE RIGHT COLLEGE.

57:40.457 --> 57:42.249
YOU HAVE A BOY
THAT LOVES YOU.

57:45.132 --> 57:48.546
YOU HAVE A BOY
THAT LOVES YOU.

57:48.546 --> 57:51.639
RIGHT? AND YOU WANT
MORE THAN THAT, RIGHT?

57:53.851 --> 57:56.183
YOU WANT TO LIVE LIFE
TO THE FULLEST.

57:57.515 --> 57:58.686
I WANT THAT, TOO.

58:01.398 --> 58:03.811
BUT, LELA,
BEING WITH THE RIGHT PERSON

58:03.811 --> 58:06.694
CAN ACTUALLY
MAKE LIFE MORE FULL.

58:06.694 --> 58:09.486
IF YOU HAVE
THE SAME PASSION,
THE SAME DRIVE.

58:11.158 --> 58:13.160
OR, MAYBE THAT
DOESN'T HELP AT ALL.

58:16.534 --> 58:18.786
YOU KNOW, MAYBE HE JUST
HAS TO RESPECT YOUR PASSION

58:18.786 --> 58:20.708
AND NOT KEEP
SECRETS FROM YOU

58:20.708 --> 58:22.379
AND GET WEIRD
WHEN YOU'RE BUSY.

58:22.379 --> 58:24.672
I-- I DON'T KNOW.
IT'S ALL PRETTY CONFUSING HERE,

58:24.672 --> 58:26.423
WHICH IS WHY
YOU SHOULD GO HOME.

58:31.969 --> 58:33.931
WHAT?
WHAT'S WRONG?

58:36.053 --> 58:38.726
YOU LOOK NORMAL.

58:38.726 --> 58:40.267
-(phone rings)
-OH.

58:42.640 --> 58:43.771
HELLO?

58:43.771 --> 58:46.063
-IT'S MACK.
-OH.

58:46.063 --> 58:48.355
-(mimics bird cawing)
-YEAH.

58:49.446 --> 58:50.778
WHAT?

58:50.778 --> 58:54.491
-HI, MACK! (laughs)
-YEAH, WE'LL BE RIGHT OVER.

58:54.491 --> 58:56.363
-TANNER, WE GOTTA GO.
COME ON!
-HUH?

58:56.363 --> 58:58.245
♪ MAMBO, MAMBO ♪

58:58.245 --> 59:00.828
♪ MAMBO ♪
(singing in Spanish)

59:00.828 --> 59:02.750
WHOO! (laughing)

59:02.750 --> 59:04.712
♪ MAMBO, MAMBO ♪

59:04.712 --> 59:06.373
(singing in Spanish)

59:06.373 --> 59:08.375
♪ MAMBO, MAMBO ♪

59:08.375 --> 59:09.927
♪ MAMBO ♪

59:12.760 --> 59:14.672
(groans)

59:15.723 --> 59:19.096
-TANNER!
-LELA, YOU LOOK LIKE
FUTURE LELA.

59:19.096 --> 59:20.848
-(clears throat) GROOVY.
-SUPER GROOVY.

59:20.848 --> 59:23.230
NO, NOT GROOVY AT ALL,
ACTUALLY. VERY UNGROOVY.

59:23.230 --> 59:25.522
SHE'S NOT SUPPOSED
TO BE ABLE TO LOOK MODERN.

59:25.522 --> 59:26.854
SMILE.

59:29.066 --> 59:32.189
-NO SHINING TEETH PANG!
-MM.

59:32.189 --> 59:33.951
-WHAT ARE YOU DOING?
-IT'S OKAY. IT'S OKAY.

59:33.951 --> 59:35.653
-WHAT ARE YOU-- STOP IT.
-JUST GO WITH IT.

59:36.994 --> 59:39.536
-HEY. WHAT-- WHAT ARE YOU--
-LOOK. WET.

59:39.536 --> 59:44.411
WHAT'S HAPPENING? WHAT ARE--
WHAT IS-- WHY IS MY HAIR
SO SQUISHY AND LIMP?

59:44.411 --> 59:46.964
I DON'T UNDERSTAND!
WHAT IS THIS FEELING?

59:46.964 --> 59:50.127
(screams)

59:50.127 --> 59:51.919
BRADY, DO YOU UNDERSTAND
WHAT'S HAPPENING?

59:51.919 --> 59:54.091
THE WHOLE ESSENCE
OF WHO THEY ARE
IS CHANGING.

59:54.091 --> 59:55.512
THEY COULD BE
STUCK HERE FOREVER,

59:55.512 --> 59:57.344
OR THE WHOLE FABRIC
OF OUR REALITY COULD
JUST RIP OPEN.

59:57.344 --> 59:59.386
-WE GOTTA GET THEM BACK.
-WELL, MAYBE WE SHOULD
JUST TELL THEM

59:59.386 --> 01:00:00.517
WHERE THEY'RE FROM,
WHAT THEY DO?

01:00:00.517 --> 01:00:02.059
ARE WE WORRIED WHAT
THAT MIGHT DO TO THEM?

01:00:02.059 --> 01:00:03.600
WELL, WE'RE RUNNING OUT
OF OPTIONS, MACK.

01:00:03.600 --> 01:00:05.893
(sighs) LELA, TANNER.

01:00:05.893 --> 01:00:08.355
YOU'RE JUST MADE-UP CHARACTERS
FROM A MOVIE. YOU ARE NOT REAL.

01:00:08.355 --> 01:00:09.526
HUH?

01:00:11.148 --> 01:00:13.781
MAYBE I WOULD'VE
EASED IT INTO THEM
A LITTLE MORE GENTLY.

01:00:13.781 --> 01:00:17.785
BUT, UH, A MOVIE?
I DON'T UNDERSTAND.

01:00:17.785 --> 01:00:19.787
-HERE. LOOK AT THIS.
-(music playing)

01:00:22.239 --> 01:00:24.041
-You like to surf?
-I know.

01:00:24.041 --> 01:00:25.913
HEY, IT'S US, DOING...

01:00:25.913 --> 01:00:28.956
THINGS WE USUALLY DO.

01:00:28.956 --> 01:00:30.457
YOU GUYS ARE
FROM AN IMAGINARY WORLD.

01:00:30.457 --> 01:00:32.960
A MOVIE WORLD.
MY FAVORITE MOVIE.
IT'S WHERE MACK AND I MET.

01:00:34.011 --> 01:00:36.593
BUT, I DON'T WANT
TO LIVE IN A MOVIE WORLD.

01:00:36.593 --> 01:00:37.925
I-- BUT, YOU DO.

01:00:37.925 --> 01:00:39.927
THAT'S WHY YOUR LIFE'S
ALWAYS BEEN SO PERFECT, LELA.

01:00:39.927 --> 01:00:41.258
IT'S WHERE YOU BELONG.

01:00:42.680 --> 01:00:44.722
(sighs)
HOW DO WE
MAKE THEM UNDERSTAND?

01:00:46.223 --> 01:00:49.026
WE COULD EXPLAIN TO THEM
IN A LANGUAGE THEY KNOW.

01:00:50.027 --> 01:00:51.228
YOU MEAN...

01:00:52.479 --> 01:00:55.192
-HERE WE GO.
-YUP.

01:01:02.079 --> 01:01:05.542
NO, YOU GUYS, HONESTLY,
LIFE IS BETTER IN A MOVIE.

01:01:05.542 --> 01:01:07.624
-YES!
-(bell rings)

01:01:07.624 --> 01:01:08.665
Man 1:
QUIET ON THE SET.

01:01:08.665 --> 01:01:10.587
-Man 2: QUIET ON THE SET.
-Man 1: PLAYBACK.

01:01:10.587 --> 01:01:11.919
-(music playing)
-Man 1: ROLL SOUND.

01:01:11.919 --> 01:01:13.500
-Man 2: SPEED.
-Man 1: ROLL CAMERA.

01:01:13.500 --> 01:01:14.591
Man 2:
ROLLING.

01:01:14.591 --> 01:01:18.595
♪ YOU GOTTA PLAY
THE SCENE ♪

01:01:18.595 --> 01:01:21.678
♪ UP ON THE SILVER SCREEN ♪

01:01:21.678 --> 01:01:25.933
- ♪ YOU GOTTA LIVE
THE DREAM ♪
-ACTION!

01:01:25.933 --> 01:01:29.016
♪ THE LIGHTS-CAMERA-
ACTION THING ♪

01:01:29.016 --> 01:01:31.358
-ROLLBACK!
- ♪ THE WATER'S
TECHNICOLOR BLUE ♪

01:01:31.358 --> 01:01:33.270
♪ AND THE WAVES
DON'T MISS A CUE ♪

01:01:33.270 --> 01:01:35.112
- ♪ NOT A HAIR
IS OUT OF PLACE ♪
-PERFECT!

01:01:35.112 --> 01:01:36.774
- ♪ EVERY LINE'S
THE PERFECT TAKE ♪
-GOOD. GO.

01:01:36.774 --> 01:01:41.118
♪ YOU GOTTA PLAY
THE SCENE ♪

01:01:41.118 --> 01:01:44.241
♪ UP ON
THE SILVER SCREEN ♪

01:01:44.241 --> 01:01:48.165
♪WHOA,
IT'S BETTER IN A STORY ♪

01:01:48.165 --> 01:01:49.877
♪ ALWAYS CLEVER,
NEVER WORDY ♪

01:01:49.877 --> 01:01:53.500
♪ YOU GOT THE PART, WHOA ♪

01:01:53.500 --> 01:01:55.422
♪ IT'S BETTER
WHEN YOU WAKE UP ♪

01:01:55.422 --> 01:01:57.254
♪ MINTY BREATH
AND PERFECT MAKEUP ♪

01:01:57.254 --> 01:01:59.296
♪ YOU'RE A WORK OF ART ♪

01:01:59.296 --> 01:02:02.679
♪ AND NO ONE EVER
BREAKS YOUR HEART ♪

01:02:02.679 --> 01:02:04.301
(slurps)

01:02:04.301 --> 01:02:08.605
♪ YOU GOTTA
PLAY THE SCENE ♪

01:02:08.605 --> 01:02:11.518
♪ UP ON
THE SILVER SCREEN ♪

01:02:11.518 --> 01:02:15.943
-♪ YEAH, YEAH ♪
-♪ NO MATTER WHERE
YOU'VE BEEN ♪

01:02:15.943 --> 01:02:19.116
♪ GOOD TIMES
ARE ZOOMING IN ♪

01:02:19.116 --> 01:02:21.278
♪ YOU CAN DREAM
BUT NO ONE SLEEPS ♪

01:02:21.278 --> 01:02:23.240
- ♪ SAY A BAD WORD
AND IT BLEEPS ♪
-(bleeps)

01:02:23.240 --> 01:02:24.862
♪ YOU CAN HAVE
AND EAT YOUR CAKE ♪

01:02:24.862 --> 01:02:26.623
♪ NEVER NEED
A BATHROOM BREAK ♪

01:02:26.623 --> 01:02:29.957
- ♪ YOU GOTTA PLAY THE SCENE ♪
-(neighs)

01:02:29.957 --> 01:02:33.871
♪ UP ON THE SILVER SCREEN ♪

01:02:33.871 --> 01:02:36.043
♪ WHOA ♪

01:02:36.043 --> 01:02:37.875
♪ IT'S BETTER
ON LOCATION ♪

01:02:37.875 --> 01:02:39.756
- ♪ 'CAUSE IT FEELS
LIKE A VACATION ♪
-(thunder crashes)

01:02:39.756 --> 01:02:43.380
♪ SUPER FUN, WHOA ♪

01:02:43.380 --> 01:02:45.222
♪ BRING THE FEATURE
TO THE PEOPLE ♪

01:02:45.222 --> 01:02:47.054
♪ IF IT'S GOOD,
THEY'LL MAKE A SEQUEL ♪

01:02:47.054 --> 01:02:49.096
♪ WHEN WE'RE DONE ♪

01:02:49.096 --> 01:02:52.389
♪ THE SURF IS UP
UNDER THE SUN ♪

01:02:52.389 --> 01:02:54.982
-(pirates shouting)
- ♪ HEY ♪

01:02:54.982 --> 01:02:56.273
♪ THE GOOD GUY
SAVES THE DAY ♪

01:02:56.273 --> 01:02:58.235
♪ THE BAD GUYS
RUN AWAY ♪

01:02:58.235 --> 01:03:01.989
♪ EVERYBODY DANCES WHEN
THE MUSIC STARTS TO PLAY ♪

01:03:11.038 --> 01:03:14.912
- ♪ HEY! HEY! ♪
-(laughs)

01:03:14.912 --> 01:03:16.753
-TANNER!
-TANNER!

01:03:16.753 --> 01:03:18.465
♪ YOUR CATS
ARE ALWAYS COOL ♪

01:03:18.465 --> 01:03:20.177
-♪ HEY! ♪
-♪ YOU NEVER HAVE
TO GO TO SCHOOL ♪

01:03:20.177 --> 01:03:22.179
-♪ YEP ♪
-♪ GET READY
FOR YOUR CLOSE UP ♪

01:03:22.179 --> 01:03:24.551
♪ IT'S THE HAPPY ENDING RULE ♪

01:03:26.013 --> 01:03:30.637
-♪ YOU GOTTA PLAY THE SCENE ♪
-♪ YOU GOTTA PLAY THE SCENE ♪

01:03:30.637 --> 01:03:34.351
-♪ YEAH ♪
-♪ UP ON THE SILVER SCREEN ♪

01:03:34.351 --> 01:03:37.895
-♪ UP ON THE SILVER SCREEN ♪
-♪ YOU GOTTA LIVE
THE DREAM ♪

01:03:37.895 --> 01:03:41.989
-♪ NO, NO, PLAY THE SCENE ♪
-♪ THE LIGHTS-CAMERA-
ACTION THING ♪

01:03:41.989 --> 01:03:44.151
♪ 'CAUSE IT'S BETTER
IN A MOVIE ♪

01:03:44.151 --> 01:03:46.113
♪ WHEN YOU MET HER
IT WAS GROOVY ♪

01:03:46.113 --> 01:03:47.824
♪ IT'S WHERE LOVE
IS ALWAYS TRUE ♪

01:03:47.824 --> 01:03:49.786
♪ WHEN YOU MET HIM
THEN YOU KNEW ♪

01:03:49.786 --> 01:03:53.710
-♪ YOU GOTTA PLAY THE SCENE ♪
-♪ PLAY THE SCENE ♪

01:03:53.710 --> 01:03:55.662
-CAN I HAVE
YOUR AUTOGRAPH?
-(screaming)

01:04:01.258 --> 01:04:04.841
♪ UP ON THE SILVER SCREEN ♪

01:04:04.841 --> 01:04:08.055
-(cheering)
-NO!

01:04:19.146 --> 01:04:22.569
I'M SORRY, BUT NO.

01:04:23.780 --> 01:04:25.862
I DON'T WANT TO BE
THAT GIRL ANYMORE.

01:04:26.863 --> 01:04:30.157
I DON'T WANT
SOMEBODY TO WRITE
MY LINES FOR ME.

01:04:31.788 --> 01:04:33.790
I WANT TO STAY HERE.

01:04:34.791 --> 01:04:36.293
FOREVER.

01:04:37.834 --> 01:04:39.496
UM-- LELA!

01:04:41.668 --> 01:04:44.501
(sighs)
WELL, THAT WAS DRAMATIC,
AND POTENTIALLY TERRIBLE.

01:04:51.178 --> 01:04:52.719
HEY, MOVE IT!
OUT OF THE WAY,
OUT OF THE WAY,

01:04:52.719 --> 01:04:54.011
OUT OF THE WAY,
OUT OF THE WAY.

01:04:54.011 --> 01:04:57.604
(grunts) OKAYS!
I THINK THERE'S ONLY
ONE THING FOR US TO DO.

01:04:57.604 --> 01:04:58.895
Group:
YEAH?

01:04:58.895 --> 01:05:01.608
AND THAT'S TO NOT
DO ANYTHINGS AND PRETEND
THAT NOTHING BAD IS HAPPENING.

01:05:01.608 --> 01:05:03.020
SOUND GOOD?
PERFECT. OKAY.

01:05:03.020 --> 01:05:05.943
BUTCHY, BUTCHY! WHOA.

01:05:05.943 --> 01:05:08.905
(panting)
OH, MY GOSH.

01:05:08.905 --> 01:05:11.989
-YOU ARE NOT
GONNA BELIEVE THIS.
-CHEECHEE, WHAT'S WRONG?

01:05:11.989 --> 01:05:14.201
WE WAS WALKING
WITH OUR PALS,
SIDECAR AND MUFFLER,

01:05:14.201 --> 01:05:16.373
AND, BOOM!
THEY JUST UP AND VANISHED.

01:05:16.373 --> 01:05:18.455
OH, THIS IS TERRIBLES.

01:05:18.455 --> 01:05:20.377
PEOPLES HAVE BEEN
DISAPPEARING LEFT AND RIGHT!

01:05:20.377 --> 01:05:23.630
-(whimpers)
-ANY ONE OF US COULD BE NEXT!

01:05:23.630 --> 01:05:24.671
OH.

01:05:27.924 --> 01:05:29.506
OKAY, THINGS STARTED
GOING WRONG

01:05:29.506 --> 01:05:32.139
EVER SINCE TANNER AND LELA
TOOK OFF INTO THE OCEAN.

01:05:32.139 --> 01:05:34.261
YOU THINKS THEMS LEAVING
IS SOMEHOW CORENATED

01:05:34.261 --> 01:05:36.813
-WITH THIS CHAIN OF EVENTS?
-YEAHS, I DO. HEY, WHAT'S THAT?

01:05:36.813 --> 01:05:37.894
Group:
OH!

01:05:46.403 --> 01:05:48.065
THIS IS THE SAME NECKLACE
MY SISTER HAD

01:05:48.065 --> 01:05:49.446
WHEN SHE DISAPPEARED
INTO THE OCEAN.

01:05:49.446 --> 01:05:53.870
MAYBE WE'S CAN USE IT, TOO.
WE CAN FIND TANNER AND LELA.

01:05:53.870 --> 01:05:56.283
WE'LL BRING 'EM BACK,
AND THEN MAYBE EVERYTHING
WILL BE NORMAL AGAIN.

01:05:56.283 --> 01:05:59.206
WE'RE LEAVING?
I GOTTA GO HOME
AND GET SOME HAIRSPRAY.

01:05:59.206 --> 01:06:01.498
-THIS DOES NOT TRAVEL WELL.
-WE AIN'T GOT TIME, CHEECH.

01:06:01.498 --> 01:06:03.420
-WHOA!
-WE GOTTA GET THERE RIGHT NOW,

01:06:03.420 --> 01:06:05.042
BEFORE MORE OF US
START DISAPPEARING.

01:06:05.042 --> 01:06:07.634
BUT, WAIT.
WHERE EXACTLY IS THERE?

01:06:07.634 --> 01:06:11.298
HOW AM I SUPPOSED
TO KNOW, STRUTS? I AIN'T
BEEN THERE, YET. COME ON.

01:06:11.298 --> 01:06:13.720
OH, YEAH.
WATER GIVES YOU
THE FEARS, DON'T IT?

01:06:13.720 --> 01:06:15.392
YEAH, IT DOES,

01:06:15.392 --> 01:06:18.645
BUT SOME THINGS
IS BIGGER THAN FEARS.

01:06:18.645 --> 01:06:22.019
-NOW, LET'S GO!
-(shouting)

01:06:23.310 --> 01:06:25.102
RIGHT.

01:06:30.867 --> 01:06:32.199
(yelps)

01:06:34.491 --> 01:06:37.374
-IT'S GONE, MACK.
-NO, IT MIGHT STILL WASH UP.

01:06:37.374 --> 01:06:39.456
LAST TIME, I ENDED UP
IN A PARALLEL MOVIE UNIVERSE.

01:06:39.456 --> 01:06:41.248
Mack: DO YOU HAVE
ANY BETTER IDEAS?
JUST KEEP LOOKING.

01:06:41.248 --> 01:06:42.669
DON'T TAKE THIS
OUT ON ME.

01:06:42.669 --> 01:06:44.791
I WASN'T THE ONE
WHO JUST BLURTED IT OUT,

01:06:44.791 --> 01:06:47.003
LIKE, "HEY,
LELA, GUESS WHAT?
YOU'RE NOT REAL."

01:06:47.003 --> 01:06:49.386
REALLY, SO THIS IS MY FAULT?
HOW ELSE SHOULD I HAVE SAID IT?

01:06:49.386 --> 01:06:51.178
I DON'T KNOW!
YOU COULD'VE BEEN
A LITTLE LESS DIRECT.

01:06:51.178 --> 01:06:54.891
LESS DIRECT, LIKE,
KEPT IT A SECRET FROM HER?
KEPT HER IN THE DARK?

01:06:54.891 --> 01:06:57.184
YEAH, 'CAUSE THAT'S
BEEN WORKING SO WELL
FOR YOU, LATELY.

01:06:57.184 --> 01:06:58.765
WELL, MAYBE WE SHOULD
GO ASK SPENCER FOR HELP.

01:06:59.766 --> 01:07:01.938
REALLY?
WE'RE BACK TO THAT?

01:07:01.938 --> 01:07:04.351
HOW ABOUT THIS?
YOU JUST KEEP LOOKING
OVER THERE.

01:07:04.351 --> 01:07:06.143
-I'MMA LOOK OVER HERE.
-YEAH, FINE BY ME.

01:07:07.734 --> 01:07:08.775
(yelps)

01:07:12.529 --> 01:07:15.072
WHAT WAS THAT ABOUT?

01:07:15.072 --> 01:07:19.366
I THINK THEY WERE ARGUING.

01:07:19.366 --> 01:07:21.078
BUT THEY'RE NOT
IN RIVAL GANGS.

01:07:22.749 --> 01:07:24.961
HERE, I GUESS,
COUPLES DO IT, TOO.

01:07:29.086 --> 01:07:30.967
I DON'T LIKE IT.

01:07:32.509 --> 01:07:34.301
ME, NEITHER.

01:07:36.673 --> 01:07:39.596
-WELL, THAT'S ODD.
-WHAT?

01:07:39.596 --> 01:07:41.438
(laughs)
WHY ARE THOSE CRAZY CATS

01:07:41.438 --> 01:07:43.270
WEARING THEIR CLOTHES
IN THE WATER?

01:07:43.270 --> 01:07:46.603
WHAT?
LELA, THOSE AREN'T CATS.

01:07:47.894 --> 01:07:50.317
-(overlapping chatter)
-WHOO-HOO-HOO! YEAH!

01:07:50.317 --> 01:07:53.650
-(gasps) THOSE ARE...
-GUYS.

01:07:53.650 --> 01:07:55.152
(gasps)

01:07:55.152 --> 01:07:57.284
-TANNER!
-LELA!

01:07:57.284 --> 01:07:59.075
-Both: OUR FRIENDS!
-OH!

01:07:59.075 --> 01:08:02.038
-TANNER! LELA!
-(cheering)

01:08:04.541 --> 01:08:06.833
THOSE PEOPLE ARE
MADE OUT OF RUBBER.

01:08:06.833 --> 01:08:09.466
(cheering continues)

01:08:11.548 --> 01:08:13.840
ARE YOU KIDDING ME?

01:08:19.805 --> 01:08:22.219
HI. HI.
COME OVER HERE.

01:08:31.608 --> 01:08:34.441
BUTCHY! LUGNUT!
CHEECHEE! STRUTS!

01:08:34.441 --> 01:08:36.823
RASCAL!
SEACAT! GIGGLES!

01:08:36.823 --> 01:08:39.656
OH, WE'S DID IT!
WE'S FOUND YOU'S GUYS.

01:08:39.656 --> 01:08:42.738
HEY, GUYS. WOW.
Y-- YOU'RE ALL HERE.

01:08:42.738 --> 01:08:44.831
WHAT ARE
YOU DOING HERE?

01:08:44.831 --> 01:08:46.292
WHAT DO YOU MEAN
WHAT ARE WE DOING HERE?

01:08:46.292 --> 01:08:48.915
-WE CAME TO TAKE
TANNER AND LELA HOME.
-Tanner: WHAT?

01:08:48.915 --> 01:08:51.508
-NO.
-Butchy: NO?

01:08:51.508 --> 01:08:53.750
I DON'T WANT
TO GO HOME, BUTCHY.

01:08:53.750 --> 01:08:55.801
BUT, LELA,
I'M YOUR BROTHER.

01:08:55.801 --> 01:08:58.515
DON'T YOU MISS ME?
DON'T YOU MISS ALL OF US?

01:08:58.515 --> 01:09:01.678
-YEAH.
-YES. OF COURSE. A LOT,

01:09:01.678 --> 01:09:06.973
BUT, WELL, I'M STARTING
TO FIND MYSELF HERE,
BUTCHY. I'M HAPPY.

01:09:07.974 --> 01:09:09.685
OKAY, LOOK, LELA,
